The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Defence deal ban on four

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Dec. 7: Four Indian firms have been banned by the defence ministry from entering into business deals with the agencies in the security establishment. 

 Officials in the defence ministry have been asked not to meet any of their representatives.

 Earlier, the defence ministry had issued a ban on South African firm Denel. 

 Denels deal to supply anti- materiel rifles to the Indian Army is being investigated by the CBI. Denel has also been prohibited from participating in the competition for an order of artillery guns.

 Defence ministry sources confirmed that Optic Electronic Private Limited, a firm based in Noida, near Delhi, has been blacklisted and that its deals are being investigated. The company is known to be a supplier and exporter of visual observation devices.

 The other companies that have been blacklisted and de-registered by the Defence Research and Development Organisation are Anika Instruments, Hace India and Reliance Fire and Safety Instruments.




